<br>
I allways thought that damage bonuses were applied directly to the damage of the weapon... which is NOT true.<br>
<br>
A damage bonus is an added amount of damage per hit (and it varies a lot).  Your offhand has no damage bonus.  Your mainhand has a damage bonus that is variable to your level.<br>
<br>
as far as 2hb goes your damage bonus will change a lot depending on the delay of your weapon (ie higher damage for lower delay weapon)<br>
<br>
Now as to how to use this practically I have no idea.  Id just go for the weapon that gives you the hihest damage bonus you can get with the lowest delay available.<br>
